cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about single image super resolution, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a deep neural network architecture with attention mechanisms, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning, cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of residual and dense connections is a common technique in deep learning, which could also place the paper in the sub-category of artificial intelligence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of multi-kernel learning, which is a technique used in neural networks for natural language processing, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on benchmark datasets, which could place it in the sub-category of multimedia, cs.MM (Multimedia).
